By  Blessing Bature-Akpakpan  | The Minister of Humanitarian Affairs, Disaster Management and Social Development, Sadiya Umar-Farouq, has condemned the killings and destruction of properties in Borno and Adamawa States. In a statement signed by the Permanent Secretary of the Ministry, Bashir Nura Alkali, the Minister, who received with shock the news of the terrorist attacks in Pemi, Chibok local government area, four other communities in Hawul local government area in Southern Borno, and Garkida in Adamawa State, described the attacks as tragic and barbaric. Umar-Farouq said, “It is really unfortunate that these terrorist attacks happened when people are expected to be enjoying the Christmas holiday with their loved ones.” She commiserated with the government and people of Borno State especially the families of the victims of the sad incident. The statement qouted the Minister as saying that the Federal Government has commended relevant authorities and the Borno State Governor,  Prof. Babagana Zulum, who immediately visited the communities and directed the strengthening of security measures in the communities. The Minister added arrangements are being made to send relief materials to the victims to cushion the effect of the attacks.  